description:
The SWICS 12-minute proton data contains densities, speeds, and thermal speeds
from the beginning of the mission up to the present day. The densities have
been cross-calibrated to the proton monitors ACE/SWEPAM and WIND/SWE, and
represent a continuous data set that can be used in conjunction with other
SWICS data, or as a stand-alone measurement. For details on the SWICS proton
data, see the release notes provided by the instrument team:
http://www.srl.caltech.edu/ACE/ASC/DATA/level2/ssprotons/swics_protons_release_notes.txt

parameters.name: nH
parameters.description: nH is the number density of Protons in the solar wind in units of #/cm^3

parameters.name: nH_err
parameters.description: nH_err is the statistical uncertainty in the number density of Protons in the solar wind, in #/cm^3

parameters.name: vH
parameters.description: vH is the mean Proton speed in the solar wind, in km/s.

parameters.name: vthH
parameters.description: vthH is the thermal speed of Protons in the solar wind, in km/s
